description: This handmade stained glass mosaic panel features a majestic Great Horned Owl among pine trees in a forest. title: Rugged Picture Jasper & Buffalo Bone Cuff: Handcrafted Men's Bracelet - Unique Masculine Jewelry Gift
description: This stunning bracelet is made up of 8mm polished Picture Jasper beads in lovely shades of brown and tan with handcarved Buffalo Bone Spacers to create a unique and powerful double strand cuff. I have used a fusion of Indigenous/Southwest/Surfer/Boho styles to create a truly unique bracelet that is both masculine and soothing. Picture Jasper carries a strong connection to Earth energies and as such can help bring harmony to your life on many levels. It is a soothing stone that brings peace and serenity, providing comfort to those who are grieving due to the loss of someone or something in their life. It diminishes feelings of loneliness, guilt or anxiety by encouraging you to focus on the present moment while clearing your mind. Picture Jasper is a relatively rare stone that forms in extremely ancient volcanic ash beds that date back to the Upper Cretaceous period, around 100 million years ago. This type of formation can be found in only one location in the world; multiple sites along the Muddy River in the desert of Jasper County, South Dakota. As such, it was prized by the Indigenous tribes in the area. Picture Jasper is said to represent the “Rainbow Bridge” connecting Heaven and Earth. It is a stone of happy dreams, as well as bringing calming reassurance during periods of stress or worry. It soothes those who are grieving the loss of a loved one and helps you to focus on the present moment rather than dwelling in what has been, or what may be. It allows for a deeper connection with the spiritual world than other stones, making it easier to communicate what you need at the time. It can also help you to ground yourself after a spirit walk or astral travel, which is the ultimate goal of journeying.

title: Ukrainian Flag Beadwoven Earrings ~ Fundraising Jewelry to Support Ukraine ~ Summer Jewelry with Meaning ~ In Clip On, Dangle or Stud Style
description: UPDATE: As of December 31, 2023 I have donated $90 to the Canadian Red Cross Ukraine Humanitarian Crisis Appeal. Thank you for your generosity. I have created these beautiful Native American fringe earrings in tribute to my many Ukrainian friends and family members. I am Metis, and growing up in Alberta, many of my best friends were either first or second generation Ukrainian. Several of my cousins have married people of Ukrainian descent, and my first serious boyfriend in University was a second generation Ukrainian who spoke his language fluently and who's mother taught me to make Ukrainian Easter Eggs the traditional way. The Ukrainian people have a long history of working alongside and befriending/marrying Native people. In fact, our "Kookum Scarves" were originally traded between the settler women from the Ukraine and our Grandmothers/Great Grandmothers because they were so beautiful. I will be donating $10 from the sale of each pair of these earrings and $5 from the "Kookum Scarf" earrings to the Canadian Red Cross Ukraine Humanitarian Crisis Appeal. These earrings are made with high quality TOHO 11/0 glass seed beads in Periwinkle Blue and Bright Yellow. I have added them to gold plated stainless steel earwires. They are 4 inches long and about 1/2 inch wide. Very light and they swing beautifully when you wear them. These are my own design and I stayed up until 2 in the morning last night designing and making them to offer as a fundraiser. You can get them on the regular earwires, on lever backs, studs or as clip-on's - your choice :)

title: The Jack Pine Stained Glass Mosaic Panel

description: This handcrafted stained glass mosaic artwork features a jack pine woodland scene reminiscent of Group of Seven artist Tom Thomson's Algonquin series of iconic paintings. It was created using hand-cut pieces of transparent and translucent stained glass adhered to the clear glass sheet permanently mounted in a recycled vintage solid wood frame (13 1/8" x 13 1/2" measured to the frame's outer edge). Once the image was created with the coloured glass, it was grouted using light beige grout. Includes a hanging kit.  Glass-on-glass (GOG) mosaics blend the transparency of modern stained glass with the intricacy of mosaics. The result is a detailed artwork that "glows" when light is transmitted thru it.  The glass artworks look beautiful when they are backlit by natural light, intended for indoor display.  All windows and most frames used for these artworks are vintage. Minor signs of age and character such as dings or scratches may be present.

title: 6" Frosted Glass Inukshuk
description: 6" Tall Frosted Glass Inukshuk Inukshuk pronounced (in-ook-shook), is a stone monument erected in the image of humans. One of their purposes was to serve as direction markers in the harsh and desolate Arctic. They were a tool of survival and a symbol of unselfish acts of the Inuit people. The Inukshuk symbolizes co-operation, balance and unselfishness; the idea that teaching and group effort is greater than individual effort. Each stone is a separate entity, yet each supports, and is supported by the one above and the one below it. No one piece is any more or any less important than the other. It’s strength lies in it’s unity. Its significance comes from its meaning as a whole. The Inukshuk reminds us of our interdependent responsibilities to invest our efforts today, to direct a better way for all of us tomorrow.

description: Jumping Bean Coffee® is a complete coffee system – an independent premium coffee roaster, specialty wholesaler, and café retailer offering the best blends and richest single origin coffees available. Independently owned and operated since 2005, Jumping Bean Coffee is an East Coast success story. Our first roast was developed by our founder and CEO Jeff LeDrew as part of his charity work during a fundraiser for the Rotary Club. From there, Jumping Bean has grown into a multi-million dollar business. Our Roast Master selects and imports the finest raw coffee beans from around the world and roasts them right here with our unique ECO2Roast® process, eliminating 85% of waste and saving a pound of carbon per pound of beans. And as of 2016, all our single serve coffee pods are manufactured with 100% compostable materials. (That’s not just biodegradable – compostable means that you can drop the whole pod, ring and all, directly into your kitchen waste or garden composter. Jumping Bean Coffee is a certified Fair Trade supplier and all our house blends are also certified Organic. Couple this with our 100% compostable single serve coffee pods, and we have a truly guilt-free cup of coffee. Other retail offerings in our cafés include a diverse line of complimentary products, including our own Floating Leaf® brand of organic teas and other premium food items. Furthermore, all of our coffee is roasted to order, with a turnaround time of 24 hours from green beans in the burlap bag to perfect coffee in your cup, so you are guaranteed the freshest possible product. When you buy from Jumping Bean, your small purchase is keeping money, jobs, and industry in Canada.

title: Golden Pearls Berry - Solanum Villosum 200 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Fruits
description: 75 days. Golden Pearls - Solanum Villosum is a fast-growing, newly discovered plant from the Solanaceae family produces clusters of sweet, yellow or orange berries, (which bear a striking resemblance to yellow currants but are no relation), on long dividing stems which carry slightly hairy leaves. It can be grown in a container, when the plant will produce fruit very quickly indeed, whilst very small, or in the open ground or greenhouse when the plant will carry on growing and producing fruit all summer long and right into the autumn. Unripe berries should not be eaten. This completely new introduction to Western gardens has been around for centuries in Africa (Solanum villosum) 6-12 hours of Sun Sprouts in 7-21 Days Ideal Temperature: 65-75 Degrees F Seed Depth: 1/8" Plant Spacing: 14" Frost Hardy: No Solanum burbankii Growing Tips: Start indoors in fine, moist soil, 6-8 weeks before setting out after frost. Harvest berries only when fully ripe, very black and soft. Warning: Avoid Eating Green Fruit!

title: Otricoli Orange Berry - Solanum Nigrum 200 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Fruits
description: Plants reach 2-3 feet tall, having typical nightshade leaves and white flowers. The small berries have a lot of visual interest being a bright orange—not at all the dark purple that you might expect. At maturity the plants are covered in clusters of brilliant orange! This species has been used as food for millenia, use only ripe fruit for eating. 70 days. 8-12 hours of Sun Sprouts in 7-21 Days Ideal Temperature: 75-85 Degrees F Seed Depth: 1/8" Plant Spacing: 14" Frost Hardy: No Solanum nigrum Growing Tips: Start indoors in fine, moist soil, 6-8 weeks before setting out after frost. Harvest berries only when fully ripe, very orange and soft. Warning: Avoid Eating Green Fruit!

title: 7.5" Clear Kiln Formed Glass Inukshuk
breadCrumbs: Home & Kitchen > Artwork
description: 7.5" Tall Glass Kin Formed Inukshuks Inukshuk pronounced (in-ook-shook), is a stone monument erected in the image of humans. One of their purposes was to serve as direction markers in the harsh and desolate Arctic. They were a tool of survival and a symbol of unselfish acts of the Inuit people. The Inukshuk symbolizes co-operation, balance and unselfishness; the idea that teaching and group effort is greater than individual effort. Each stone is a separate entity, yet each supports, and is supported by the one above and the one below it. No one piece is any more or any less important than the other. It’s strength lies in it’s unity. Its significance comes from its meaning as a whole. The Inukshuk reminds us of our interdependent responsibilities to invest our efforts today, to direct a better way for all of us tomorrow.

description: Peace by Chocolate is a story of resilience, community, and the transformative power of kindness. Founded by the Hadhad family, Syrian refugees who resettled in Antigonish, Nova Scotia, Peace by Chocolate grew from humble beginnings to a celebrated chocolatier with a mission. The family’s chocolate-making roots run deep, tracing back over 30 years to their factory in Damascus, Syria. Forced to leave everything behind during the Syrian civil war, they found themselves starting over in Canada, where they shared their passion for artisanal chocolate with their new community. Their neighbors embraced them, and with that support, Peace by Chocolate blossomed into a symbol of hope and unity, bridging cultures through the universal love of chocolate. Each product crafted by Peace by Chocolate carries a message of inclusivity, peace, and quality. From classic milk chocolate to innovative flavors like maple cream, dark chocolate with sea salt, and tiramisu, every bar is made with ethically sourced ingredients and a dedication to sustainable practices. Their “Peace Bars,” such as the “Give’r” maple cream bar, celebrate Canadian spirit, while the “Happy Birthday” and “Tiramisu” bars add a touch of joy to any occasion. With every purchase, customers are not only indulging in premium chocolate but also supporting a movement that champions inclusion, peacebuilding, and giving back. Peace by Chocolate is a testament to how shared dreams and community support can create something truly sweet and meaningful.

title: Garden Huckleberry - Solanum Melanocerasum Berry 200 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Fruits
description: Solanum melanocerasum. Garden Huckleberry seeds are started indoors around the same time as tomato seeds. Transplant out in mid-May to June, with your tomato seedlings. The small, 1cm (1/2”) fruits begin to set early, turning from bright green to jet black. These hold on the plant, even if they appear early in the season. We recommend waiting until after the first frost to harvest all at once the fruits that have turned black. It’s a fruit for cooking and sweetening, with a flavour reminiscent of blueberries and Concorde grapes. These work well in pies and preserves, but require the same kind of help with sweetening that rhubarb does. Like tomatoes and eggplants, this is a member of the nightshade family, so care should be taken not to eat unripened or uncooked fruits Do not eat fruits with any green skin showing, as they are slightly toxic. The compact annual bushes grow with a height and spread around 60cm (24”) each. The tiny seeds are easy to save for planting the following year. Some references confusingly list “wonderberry” as a synonym for this plant, but wonderberry is a hybridized variant. The common name Garden Huckleberry is also applied in some references to Solanum scabrum, a related plant grown as a leaf crop. Our Garden Huckleberry is native to Africa, and is not a true huckleberry, nor is it a ground cherry. Matures 80 days from transplant. (Open-pollinated seeds) Warning: Avoid Eating Green Fruit!

title: Hudson Bay Blanket Seed Bead Earrings ~ Native American/Cottagecore Handmade Gift For Her ~ Vintage Canadiana in Clip On, Dangle or Studs
description: Inspired by the iconic Hudson's Bay 4 Point Trading Blanket, these seed bead earrings are a true Canadian product. Handmade by me, a Metis woman who is married to a traditional Metis trapper (retired), these earrings bring thoughts of sitting by a fire wrapped up in this thick wool blanket. This was a much sought-after trade item between the Hudson's Bay Company fur traders and the local Indigenous people throughout Canada during the early fur trading years. The Hudson's Bay Blanket was used to make warm Capotes (Metis Blanket Coats) and gloves as well as gracing the beds in trappers cabins. The colours of the blanket - white with red, green, yellow and black stripes is STILL the corporate colours of The Bay stores. After incorporation by English royal charter in 1677, the company functioned as the de facto government in parts of North America for nearly 200 years until the HBC sold the land it owned (the entire Hudson Bay drainage basin, known as Rupert's Land) to Canada in 1869 as part of the Deed of Surrender. At its peak, the company controlled the fur trade throughout much of the English- and later British-controlled North America. By the mid-19th century, the company evolved into a mercantile business selling a wide variety of products from furs to fine homeware in a small number of sales shops (as opposed to trading posts) across Canada. These shops were the first step towards the department stores the company owns today. The earwire or posts (if you choose studs) are silver plated stainless steel. The triangle frame and small silver feather charm are silver plated brass. The seed beads are all glass 11/0 size. The earrings have 13 fringes each and are 5.5 inches long and 1 inch wide. You can choose these earrings as Dangle, Stud or Clip-on style - whichever suits you :)

title: FLORA Organic Calendula Oil double infused in Organic Olive Oil -100% Natural Moisturizer - Made in Canada. 50 ml
breadCrumbs: Beauty & Personal Care > Skin Care > Body > Moisturizers > Oils
description: Our naturally-grown deep orange Calendula officinalis flower heads (seeds & petals) are slowly double-infused (2x6 weeks) into cold-pressed certified organic olive oil at a controlled temperature for optimum extraction. We produce our plant oils only in small batches using organic and responsibly sourced ingredients. This is not an essential oil as Calendula flowers are low in volatile compounds (~0.2%) and render low distillation rates. The unique way to capture all the botanicals contained in this plant is to slowly extract the whole flower heads (seeds & petals) into an oil that promotes Calendula's beneficial properties. Calendula is a well-known versatile plant beneficial for dry and damaged skin. Calendula oil can be used as it is, in massage mixtures with other oils, or for the enrichment of skincare products (salves, creams, masks). To preserve and maintain the beneficial properties of Calendula oil for years, we package our oils in light-resistant, amber glass bottles which prevent light degradation. Our Calendula Oil is made at a botanical extract ratio of 1:5, which means 1-part Calendula flowers to 5-parts Olive oil which translates to 17% Calendula in each bottle. We do not include any fragrance or extracts in our oils to make them suitable for delicate baby skin as well as, sensitive skin.

description: This handmade stained glass panel features a representation of the northern lights (aurora borealis) with a mountain and a frozen landscape.  The mosaic has been created by hand-cutting stained glass, adhering it to a plain glass sheet, and finished with dark-colored grout and hand-painted details on mountains. The mosaic is permanently mounted in a vintage solid wood frame (13 1/2" x 11 1/2" - Measured to the outer edge of the frame.). The panel includes a hanging kit.  A glass on glass (GOG) mosaic blends the transparency of modern stained glass with the intricacy of mosaics. The result is a detailed piece of artwork that "glows" when light is transmitted thru it.  The glass artworks look beautiful when they are backlit by natural light. Intended for indoor display.  All windows and most frames used for these artworks are vintage. Subtle imperfections and signs of character may be present.

title: Tim Hortons Decaf Coffee, Single Serve Keurig K Cup Pods, Medium Roast, 72 Count 6
breadCrumbs: Grocery & Gourmet Food > Beverages > Coffee > Single-Serve Capsules & Pods
description: Tim Hortons is Canada’s favorite coffee for a reason. For over 50 years, we have overseen every step in our coffee process to ensure we offer you the quality you deserve. Now you can make your favorite Tim Hortons brew at home, your way! Our coffee grounds can be used with a filter in automatic coffee makers, in a french press, as a pourover, or even to make cold brew coffee. We roast our own beans to ensure your coffee will taste the same cup after cup. Tim Hortons is happy to serve you coffee with care, from bean to cup and invite you to share our sentiment of positivity and togetherness with your community. In 1964, celebrated hockey legend Tim Horton opened our first coffee shop in a small town in Canada, serving our “Always Fresh” premium coffee blends to coffee-loving Canadians. Today Tim’s vision of creating a place where everyone was welcome to come in and enjoy a cup of coffee has spread to locations throughout Canada, the U.S., and now, the world. We are proud to serve you an amazing cup of coffee whether you enjoy it as your morning wakeup call or as an afternoon pick-me-up, from home, or from one of our worldwide locations.

title: Nabob Medium Roast 1896 Tradition Ground Coffee, 340g Canister
breadCrumbs: Grocery & Gourmet Food > Beverages > Coffee > Ground Coffee
description: Explore the flavours of the world from your home with Nabob Ground Coffee. Nabob Medium Roast 1896 Tradition Ground Coffee is made from sustainably sourced 100% Arabica beans. More than 115 years of know-how help us roast this perfectly balanced coffee, with delicate notes of cocoa and citrus. Original coffee from our master roasters, this blend is perfect for people who appreciate classic coffees. Nabob ground coffee is 100% Rainforest Alliance Certified, demonstrating our commitment to both the environment and great coffee. Our recyclable canister packaging is made with 80% paper-fiber from renewable resources (excludes freshness seal). To prepare, use two level tablespoons of ground coffee per 8 oz (250 mL) of cold, fresh and filtered water. The flavour-lock pack keeps your coffee fresh in between cups. For optimal freshness, brew the coffee within a week of opening the package. Proudly roasted and packaged in Ontario, Canada, our coffee is Certified Kosher. Ever since our beginnings back in 1896, the Nabob Coffee Co. continues to fuel our passion for coffee, our communities and the environment.

title: Jumping Bean Deep Water Fairtrade Organic Whole Bean Coffee, ECO2Roast, Premium Coffee, Made in Canada, Non-GMO, Deep Water Dark , 454g
breadCrumbs: Grocery & Gourmet Food > Beverages > Coffee > Whole Coffee Beans > Whole Beans
description: Jumping Bean Coffee® is a complete coffee system – an independent premium coffee roaster, specialty wholesaler, and café retailer offering the best blends and richest single origin coffees available. Independently owned and operated since 2005, Jumping Bean Coffee is an East Coast success story. Our first roast was developed by our founder and CEO Jeff LeDrew as part of his charity work during a fundraiser for the Rotary Club. From there, Jumping Bean has grown into a multi-million dollar business. Our Roast Master selects and imports the finest raw coffee beans from around the world and roasts them right here with our unique ECO2Roast® process, eliminating 85% of waste and saving a pound of carbon per pound of beans. And as of 2016, all our single serve coffee pods are manufactured with 100% compostable materials. (That’s not just biodegradable – compostable means that you can drop the whole pod, ring and all, directly into your kitchen waste or garden composter. Jumping Bean Coffee is a certified Fair Trade supplier and all our house blends are also certified Organic. Couple this with our 100% compostable single serve coffee pods, and we have a truly guilt-free cup of coffee. Other retail offerings in our cafés include a diverse line of complimentary products, including our own Floating Leaf® brand of organic teas and other premium food items. Furthermore, all of our coffee is roasted to order, with a turnaround time of 24 hours from green beans in the burlap bag to perfect coffee in your cup, so you are guaranteed the freshest possible product. When you buy from Jumping Bean, your small purchase is keeping money, jobs, and industry in Canada.

description: French's Tomato Ketchup is free from artificial flavours, artificial colours, gluten and high fructose corn syrup for unrivaled quality and a taste you'll love. Made using fresh tomatoes for unforgettable flavour, French's Tomato Ketchup has a rich, thick consistency and sweet, tangy tomato flavour. Ketchup is high on the list of best sauces for a range of eating outlets — and for a good reason. When it comes to eating this sweet and tangy condiment for a dipping sauce, the options are endless. Use real tomato ketchup as a dipping sauce for favourites like mozzarella sticks and tater tots. French's Tomato Ketchup is excellent with fries and chicken fingers or for topping burgers and sandwiches. Place ketchup bottles in table caddies and at self-serve condiment stations so all your guests can enjoy the sweet and tangy flavour of this ketchup. French's Tomato Ketchup comes in a pack of squeeze bottles perfect for high-volume eating establishments and busy kitchens. Tomato ketchup squeeze bottles have a similar appeal to bulk ketchup packets when it comes to giving your guests the power to apportion as much or as little as they'd like. French's real tomato ketchup is kosher, dairy-free, gluten-free, non-GMO project verified, and free from allergens, artificial flavours, artificial colours and high fructose corn syrup.

breadCrumbs: Grocery & Gourmet Food > Beverages > Coffee > Single-Serve Capsules & Pods
description: Jumping Bean Coffee® is a complete coffee system – an independent premium coffee roaster, specialty wholesaler, and café retailer offering the best blends and richest single origin coffees available. Independently owned and operated since 2005, Jumping Bean Coffee is an East Coast success story. Our first roast was developed by our founder and CEO Jeff LeDrew as part of his charity work during a fundraiser for the Rotary Club. From there, Jumping Bean has grown into a multi-million dollar business. Our Roast Master selects and imports the finest raw coffee beans from around the world and roasts them right here with our unique ECO2Roast® process, eliminating 85% of waste and saving a pound of carbon per pound of beans. And as of 2016, all our single serve coffee pods are manufactured with 100% compostable materials. (That’s not just biodegradable – compostable means that you can drop the whole pod, ring and all, directly into your kitchen waste or garden composter. Jumping Bean Coffee is a certified Fair Trade supplier and all our house blends are also certified Organic. Couple this with our 100% compostable single serve coffee pods, and we have a truly guilt-free cup of coffee. Other retail offerings in our cafés include a diverse line of complimentary products, including our own Floating Leaf® brand of organic teas and other premium food items. Furthermore, all of our coffee is roasted to order, with a turnaround time of 24 hours from green beans in the burlap bag to perfect coffee in your cup, so you are guaranteed the freshest possible product. When you buy from Jumping Bean, your small purchase is keeping money, jobs, and industry in Canada.

title: Tiny Tim Micro Dwarf Tomato 40 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Vegetables
description: Tiny Tim is a compact micro dwarf tomato variety perfect for small spaces, container gardening, and indoor growing. This heirloom variety grows to only 12-18 inches (30-45 cm) tall, making it ideal for patios, balconies, and even windowsills. Despite its small size, Tiny Tim produces abundant clusters of sweet, bright red cherry tomatoes with a well-balanced flavor. This determinate variety is fast-growing, highly productive, and thrives in both outdoor and indoor environments, making it a favorite among home gardeners. (Open-pollinated) Planting Instructions: 1. Growing Conditions: Hardiness Zones: Suitable for USDA zones 3-10 (typically grown as an annual) Sunlight: Requires 6-8 hours of full sun daily Soil: Well-draining, nutrient-rich soil with a pH of 6.0-6.8 Container Size: A 1-2 gallon container is sufficient for a single plant Spacing: If planted in garden beds, space 12 inches apart 2. Sowing & Germination: Indoor Start: Begin seeds 4-6 weeks before the last frost date. Sowing Depth: Plant seeds ¼ inch (6 mm) deep in seed-starting mix. Temperature: Keep soil between 70-80°F (21-27°C) for germination. Germination Time: 5-10 days under optimal conditions. 3. Transplanting & Care: Hardening Off: Before moving outdoors, gradually expose seedlings to outside conditions over 7-10 days. Watering: Keep soil evenly moist but avoid overwatering. Fertilizing: Use a balanced fertilizer every 2-3 weeks or an organic compost-rich mix. Support: Tiny Tim has a bushy growth habit and generally does not require staking. Pruning: Minimal pruning is needed, but removing yellowing leaves can improve air circulation. 4. Harvesting: Time to Maturity: 45-55 days from planting. Harvesting Tip: Pick tomatoes when they turn bright red for the best flavor. Continuous Harvest: Regular picking encourages further production. Why Grow Tiny Tim? Perfect for small spaces & container gardening Fast-growing & high-yielding Suitable for indoor & outdoor growing No staking required, low-maintenance Produces delicious, sweet cherry tomatoes With its compact size and impressive yield, Tiny Tim is an excellent choice for home gardeners looking to enjoy fresh tomatoes in limited spaces!

title: Peruvian Physalis - Physalis peruviana – Golden Berry - Cape Gooseberry - Inca Berry 100 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Fruits
description: Physalis peruviana, commonly known as Golden Berry, Cape Gooseberry, or Inca Berry, is a small, bright orange fruit encased in a delicate, papery husk. Native to South America, it belongs to the nightshade family (Solanaceae) and is prized for its sweet-tart flavor, rich in vitamin C and antioxidants. The plant grows as a bushy, fast-growing perennial in warm climates but is often cultivated as an annual in cooler regions. It reaches 2 to 3 feet (60–90 cm) in height and produces small, yellow bell-shaped flowers before fruit formation. Planting Instructions: 1. Starting from Seeds: Timing: Start seeds indoors 6–8 weeks before the last frost if growing in temperate regions. Germination: Seeds germinate in 7–14 days at temperatures between 70–85°F (21–29°C). Soil: Use well-draining, nutrient-rich soil with a pH of 5.5–7.0. Depth: Sow seeds ¼ inch (6 mm) deep in seed-starting trays or small pots. Light: Provide bright light or use a grow light for healthy seedling development. 2. Transplanting: Once seedlings have at least two sets of true leaves, harden them off before transplanting outdoors. Space plants 2–3 feet (60–90 cm) apart in a sunny location. Choose a site with full sun (at least 6–8 hours per day). Provide well-draining, sandy or loamy soil with compost for best growth. 3. Care & Maintenance: Watering: Keep soil evenly moist but avoid waterlogging. Mulching: Add a layer of mulch to retain moisture and suppress weeds. Support: Provide stakes or cages to support branches laden with fruit. Fertilization: Use a balanced fertilizer every 2–4 weeks during active growth. 4. Harvesting: Time to Maturity: 70–90 days from transplanting. When to Harvest: Berries are ripe when the husk turns brown and papery, and the fruit inside is golden-yellow. Storage: Fruits can be eaten fresh, dried, or stored in their husks for several weeks in a cool, dry place. Additional Notes: Cold Sensitivity: This plant is frost-sensitive and should be brought indoors or grown in a greenhouse in colder regions. Self-Pollinating: Flowers attract pollinators, but the plant is self-fertile and does not require cross-pollination. Uses: Great for fresh eating, jams, desserts, and dried snacks. Physalis peruviana is a highly rewarding plant, perfect for home gardeners looking to grow an exotic, nutritious fruit!

title: Hardy Kiwi Berry 50 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Fruits
description: Fruit grows just like grapes. The decorative vines are covered with lovely white flowers in spring, with a fragrance like Lily-of-the-Valley. The fruit is smooth- skinned and therefore does not require peeling.The fruit averages 5 cm (2 in) in size. Plants should be spaced at least 2 m (6 ft) apart. How to grow Hardy Kiwi Berry from seed: Place the seeds in a container with moist perlite and refrigerate at 40°F (4°C) for 2 months. Plant the seeds 1/8 inch deep in moist sterile potting mix and cover the container with plastic wrap. Check seeds weekly and re-moisten perlite as needed. Place the container in a warm, bright spot and keep the soil moist. When seedlings start growing, uncover the container. When the plants have four true leaves, transplant them into individual pots. When the plants are several inches tall, transplant them outdoors when risk of frost has passed. Plant in a location that is protected from strong winds and has a sunny location. Both male and female plants are needed for proper pollination. Space plants 5 – 10 feet apart, further if space is available. When planting the roots make sure the CROWN is at soil level! Kiwis grow very similar to grapes and may be treated the same way. They bear fruit on 2 year old wood, but it usually takes 3 or more years to bring a plant into production. In the first year establish a main stem about 4 – 5 feet high, once it reaches this height pinch the top couple of inches, this will encourage branching. The following seasons you want the plant to branch out laterally. These lateral branches will produce fruiting canes. After a cane bears fruit, remove that cane, this will allow more space for new canes to produce. Fertilize regularly with Fruit Tree & Shrub Fertilizer. For the first winter we suggest you lay the vine down and cover it with leaves. During fruiting periods make sure the vines get ample amount of water, to ensure proper fruit formation. Hardy Perennial Zone 3-9 Years to maturity 3-4

description: Signet Marigold (Tagetes tenuifolia 'Orange Gem') is a compact, bushy annual known for its delicate, lacy foliage and vibrant orange, single-petaled flowers. The blooms have a citrusy fragrance, making them a favorite for pollinators like bees and butterflies. This variety is edible, adding a mild, citrus-like flavor to salads and dishes. It thrives in garden beds, borders, and containers, providing season-long color with continuous blooms until frost. Planting Instructions: 1. Starting Seeds Indoors (Optional): Start seeds indoors 4–6 weeks before the last frost date in well-draining seed-starting mix. Plant seeds ¼ inch deep and keep the soil moist. Maintain a temperature of 65–75°F (18–24°C) for germination, which takes 5–10 days. Transplant seedlings outdoors after the danger of frost has passed. 2. Direct Sowing Outdoors: After the last frost, sow seeds directly into well-prepared, loose, well-draining soil. Plant seeds ¼ inch deep, spacing them 8–12 inches apart. Water lightly and keep soil moist until seedlings emerge. 3. Growing Conditions: Sunlight: Full sun (at least 6–8 hours of direct sunlight daily). Soil: Prefers well-draining, moderately fertile soil with a pH of 6.0–7.0. Watering: Keep the soil evenly moist but avoid overwatering. Drought-tolerant once established. Fertilization: A light application of a balanced fertilizer can boost growth but avoid excess nitrogen. 4. Maintenance: Deadhead spent flowers to encourage continuous blooming. Pinch back young plants to promote bushier growth. Resistant to most pests but can deter unwanted insects in the garden. 5. Harvesting and Uses: Flowers and leaves are edible, adding a subtle citrus flavor to dishes. Makes an excellent companion plant for vegetables by repelling pests. Enjoy 'Orange Gem' Signet Marigolds for their beauty, fragrance, and edible blooms in both ornamental and functional gardens!

title: Black Strawberry Tomato 40 Seeds
breadCrumbs: Patio, Lawn & Garden > Plants, Seeds & Bulbs > Vegetables
description: The Black Strawberry Tomato is a stunning cherry tomato variety known for its unique, rich color and exceptional flavor. The fruits ripen to a deep mahogany with hints of purple and red, resembling the hues of a strawberry. These small, juicy tomatoes are bursting with a complex, sweet, and tangy taste, making them perfect for fresh eating, salads, and garnishes. The determinate plants produce high yields of trusses loaded with clusters of these eye-catching fruits. Planting Instructions: 1. Growing Conditions: Hardiness Zone: Best grown as an annual in USDA zones 3-10 Sunlight: Full sun (at least 6-8 hours daily) Soil: Well-draining, nutrient-rich soil with a pH of 6.0-6.8 Spacing: 18-24 inches apart for good airflow and growth 2. Sowing Seeds: Start seeds indoors 6-8 weeks before the last frost date. Plant seeds ¼ inch deep in seed-starting mix and keep soil moist. Maintain a temperature of 70-80°F (21-27°C) for germination, which takes 5-10 days. Provide grow lights or a sunny windowsill to promote strong seedlings. 3. Transplanting: After the last frost, harden off seedlings by gradually exposing them to outdoor conditions over 7-10 days. Transplant them into the garden or large containers once nighttime temperatures remain above 50°F (10°C). Plant deeply, burying the stem up to the first set of true leaves to encourage strong root development. 4. Care & Maintenance: Watering: Keep soil evenly moist but avoid overwatering. Mulching: Apply mulch around plants to retain moisture and prevent weeds. Support: Use stakes, cages, or trellises as this is an indeterminate variety that will continue growing and producing throughout the season. Fertilizing: Use a balanced fertilizer or compost every 2-3 weeks for optimal growth and fruiting. Pruning: Remove lower leaves and suckers to improve airflow and prevent disease. 5. Harvesting: Tomatoes are ready to harvest when they turn a rich mahogany red with hints of purple. Pick regularly to encourage continuous fruit production. Enjoy these delicious, exotic-looking tomatoes fresh off the vine or in gourmet dishes!
